    _class: 'uk.magicmamaliga.backend.record.model.Recording',
    summary: 'Angela introduces two newly hired customer care teammates, Ken and Maria, and Tarek from the customer care team. Tarek then takes the floor to cover onboarding requirements: there are liability policy and confidentiality agreement forms that must be read, signed electronically, and returned before work can begin. Maria says she didn’t receive the document; Tarek will resend it today. The document requires four initials and two signatures. Signed copies should be emailed to Tarek.godas at mail.ca. Action items: Maria to sign and return the form this afternoon; Ken to confirm the email address on file. Tarek leaves to wrap up onboarding details.\n' +
      '\n' +
      'Back in the main agenda, Angela outlines Ken and Maria’s roles: they will handle client inquiries, work with team leads and other customers, and provide short demos of Logiteam. Over the next two weeks, they will become Logiteam experts, familiar with basic functions, security features, add-ons, and common glitches, so they can assist clients effectively by the end of training. Questions are invited.\n' +
      '\n' +
      'During Q&A, Ken asks whether they should use personal devices or the company laptop; the answer is they will use a company-provided setup, and accounts will be created on the work computer. Another question about client contact methods; the response is that a video conferencing tool will be used and covered in training.\n' +
      '\n' +
      'Product background is provided: Jen and Nina founded the company three years ago, created Logiteam for training work teams. The company now has 43 employees, 82 customers, and five product packages. The training is designed to prepare Ken and Maria to demonstrate and support the software to its full potential.',
    title: 'Introducing New Customer Care Team Members and Training'
